  "title": "Construction Project Manager | Start Immediate | Cable Industry",
  "description": "<p><strong>Construction Project Manager</strong><br /><strong>Salary : $6,500 - $8,000</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Job Descriptions:</strong></p><ul><li>Build and develop the project team to ensure maximum performance, by providing purpose, direction, and motivation.</li><li>Lead projects from requirements definition through deployment, identifying schedules, scopes, budget estimations, and implementation plans, including risk mitigation.</li><li>Coordinate internal and external resources to ensure that projects adhere to scope, schedule, and budget.</li><li>Report project outcomes and/or risks to the appropriate management channels and escalate issues, as necessary, according to project work plan.</li><li>To attend site meetings with client and/or Sub-Contractor(s) whenever necessary with regards to any site issues.</li><li>To make sure site work progress follows the Schedule given by the Main Contractor.</li><li>To prepare monthly Cashflow, Progress Claims, Payment Certificates, etc.</li><li>To manage and review Sub-Contractor(s) and their monthly performance.</li><li>To prepare Method of Statement as and when necessary, for specific works.</li><li>To manage workers’ working time and do not work unnecessary overtime. Any overtime works must be first approved by the Managing Director before commencement.</li><li>To report daily progress and weekly progress status to project director.</li><li>Any other ad hoc duties assigned by the Project Director.</li></ul><p><br /><br />Chin Wan Chee, Racheal  (R25157940)<br />Business Edge Personnel Services Pte Ltd (96C4864)</p>",
